From ac6befbfac3ea98043c745cee4ad32d2461ec805 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Hari Naraayana Desikan Kannan <hnaraaya@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Sat, 20 Sep 2025 14:17:32 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL: wifi: ath12k: Skip links marked for
 removal during ML reconfig when selecting next primary

During MLO reconfiguration, when the current primary link is removed,
ath12k_mac_get_next_pri_link() selects the next primary link from the
current active links. However, some of these links may also be marked
for removal as part of the same ML reconfiguration, which can result in
choosing a primary link that will not exist after the
ML reconfiguration.

Fix this by excluding links listed in ML reconfiguration when
choosing the next primary link. This ensures the new primary link will
remain valid after ML reconfiguration completes.

Signed-off-by: Hari Naraayana Desikan Kannan <hnaraaya@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
@@ -12726,10 +12726,13 @@ static int ath12k_mac_get_next_pri_link(
 		   ahsta->primary_link_id, curr_links, sta->addr);
 
 	/* exclude the current primary link id from consideration */
 	links_map = curr_links & ~BIT(ahsta->primary_link_id);
 
+	/* Also exclude any links marked for removal in ML reconfig */
+	links_map &= ~sta->reconf.removed_links;
+
 	/* if only no link is available then can not really migrate*/
 	if (!links_map)
 		return -EINVAL;
 
 	*pri_link_id = ath12k_mac_ahsta_get_pri_link_id(ahvif, ahsta, links_map);
